From bb17c5109ef39e346a57975459ae828dda9fb4a3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Daniel Golle <daniel@makrotopia.org>
Date: Tue, 24 Feb 2026 02:51:26 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 24/26] doc: bootstd: add OpenWrt boot method documentation

Document the OpenWrt boot method (bootmeth_openwrt) which boots
OpenWrt-style uImage.FIT firmware images containing kernel, device tree
and read-only root filesystem in a single container.

The document describes how the bootmeth uses the imagemap abstraction to
access FIT images on block devices, MTD partitions and UBI volumes, how
dm-verity command-line parameters are generated from FIT metadata, and
how on-demand loading avoids reading filesystem sub-images that Linux
maps directly from flash.

Signed-off-by: Daniel Golle <daniel@makrotopia.org>
