+
+OpenWrt Bootmeth
+================
+
+OpenWrt uses a single :doc:`/usage/fit/index` container that bundles the Linux
+kernel, one or more device-tree blobs and a read-only root filesystem into one
+monolithic firmware image.  At boot the kernel maps the embedded filesystem
+directly from flash via the Linux uImage.FIT block driver (exposing it as
+``/dev/fit0``, ``/dev/fit1``, …).  No separate boot partition, boot filesystem
+or initramfs is required.
+
+The same ``.itb`` image can be stored on a block-device partition, a raw MTD
+partition or a UBI volume, making the format boot-medium agnostic.
+
+When invoked on a bootdev, this bootmeth uses the *imagemap* abstraction layer
+to access the FIT image on the underlying storage.  During
+``read_bootflow()`` the imagemap is created and the FIT header is read to
+verify that a valid FIT is present.  For block devices the GPT partition label
+is used as the image name.
+
+When the bootflow is booted, the bootmeth performs the following steps:
+
+1. An imagemap device is created for the boot storage and a
+   ``struct bootm_info`` is allocated and initialised.
+
+2. The optional ``bootconf`` environment variable is read.  If set, it selects
+   a specific FIT configuration (passed as the ``#<conf>`` suffix to bootm).
+
+3. The FIT structure block is read through the imagemap so that dm-verity
+   metadata can be extracted before entering the bootm state machine.  For each
+   ``filesystem`` loadable that carries a ``dm-verity`` subnode,
+   ``fit_verity_build_params()`` generates ``dm-mod.create`` and
+   ``dm-mod.waitfor`` kernel command-line parameters (see
+   :doc:`/usage/fit/dm-verity`).
+
+4. Depending on whether dm-verity targets were found, ``root=`` is set to
+   ``/dev/dm-0`` (verity) or ``/dev/fit0`` (plain), and ``rootwait`` is added.
+
+5. ``bootm_run()`` is called.  The imagemap enables on-demand loading so that
+   only the kernel and FDT sub-images are actually read from storage; filesystem
+   sub-images are skipped because Linux maps them directly from the same flash.
+
+6. After ``bootm_run()`` returns (on failure), the imagemap and allocated
+   structures are freed.
+
+The compatible string "u-boot,openwrt" is used for the driver.  It is present
+if ``CONFIG_BOOTMETH_OPENWRT`` is enabled.  The driver additionally depends on
+``CONFIG_FIT``, ``CONFIG_BOOTSTD`` and ``CONFIG_IMAGEMAP``.
